(1919 - 2004) als politische Poesie des vermeintlich Unpolitischen. In drei Hauptkapiteln werden drei verschiedene Modi der Kritik herausgearbeitet, die verdeutlichen, wie Sophia Andresen die poetische Form als Form geistigen Widerstands in einer bis heute zutiefst beeindruckenden Konsequenz umgesetzt hat.  aThis is the first comprehensive study by German-speaking Portuguese scholars on Sophia de Mello Breyner Andresen (1919–2004), one of the most acclaimed Portuguese poets of the 20th century. It presents a re-evaluation of her work as a political poetry of the putative a-political.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAndresen, Sophia de Mello Breyner-Criticism and interpretation. 0aPortuguese poetry-20th century-History and criticism. 4aEstado Novo. 4aPortugiesische Lyrik. 4aSchreiben in Diktaturen. 4aSophia de Mello Breyner Andresen. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh  aEstado Novo.  aPortuguese poetry.  aSophia de Mello Breyner Andresen.  aliterature under dictatorship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105229520 cprintz978311052282240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311052514440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110525144423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110525144/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBK